public class UIError : MonoBehaviour
{
    public Text scoreText;

    void Start()
    {
        // Forgot to assign scoreText in Inspector!
        scoreText.text = "Score: 0";  // NullReferenceException!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
You're trying to use a Text component that was never assigned.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void Start()
{
    if (scoreText != null)
    {
        scoreText.text = "Score: 0";
    }
    else
    {
        Debug.LogError("scoreText is not assigned!");
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if UI references are assigned before using them."
